div.p: 1) How does a deck relate to a game?
A deck is used in a game. The deck belongs to the game, a game contains a deck/decks.
2) How does a card relate to a deck?
3) What properties would a game have?
A game keeps track of score. The game has the deck of cards. Players. The game would have rules about blackjack.
4) What properties does a card have?
A card has a value associated with scoring. Cards (deck) can be shuffled. Cards can be dealt. Cards have suites/face/number.
